Starting in 1956, the PTA made a significant contribution to the crowned development of the RM Meteorological Fusion (Rakeita Meteorologicalzna), which became the first Polish Fusion to carry out scientific research.
The first model, RM-1, was completed in 1957 and the first launch took place on October 10, 1958.
This 1,800-metre gap had a length of 80 cm and weighed a little less than 5 kg.
