This fuse had a length of 1.4 meters and probably weighed 11.5 kg.
The following prototype should have been able to do concrete scientific work - the RM-34 rocket should have a range of up to 14.5 km and be used to observe the wind at altitude.
But in 1963 all development work was stopped.
The Meteor-1 Fusion was developed during the period 1962 - 1965, followed by the first RM-type Fusions.
It was designed with two floors and had a total length of 510 cm and an initial weight of 32.5 kg.
Three models (called Meteor-1A, -1B and -1C) were developed; they were distinguished by the dimensions of the space reserved for scientific tools.
