Hector "Hetin" Reyes "The basketball is all my life"
The "Hetin" Reyes basketball ballooner spent more than 60 years of his life in relation to the ground and, thanks to him, travelled around the world.
Few people in Puerto Rico have a knowledge of the history of the local basketball as big as that of Hector "Hetin" Reyes.
The reason is that before a brain hemorrhage does not condemn him to the wheelchair running in 2008, Reyes was immersed in this sport for more than 60 years, whether as a lower league player, player of the national basketball team, manager and leader of the national team, the BSN, with the Vaqueros de Bayamón or as president of the basketball federation.
