"The basketball is my whole life."
Reyes does not exaggerate when he makes that statement.
The walls of his house, almost all decorated with photos and memories that remind him of his journey out of standards, testify to this.
Bayamón in the Heart
Of all his memories, the ones he most loves are those who remind him of his passage as a player in the Vakuros team in the mid-50s until 1982, after having spent 15 years as co-managed or manager of the team.
"That was my best years, the ones that I enjoyed most because I had the chance to participate in eight Vaqueros championships since 1967, whether as manager, co-manager or leader.
