I recall when we won it for the first time in the United States at the pre-Olympics tournament in Mexico in 1989.
Then there was the 1990 World Cup, where we arrived 4th and where we should have won the bronze medal if this Canadian judge had not brought us back to our last match, Reyes said.
Is the 1990 World Team the best national team you've ever seen?
It is among the best, as was the one that beat the Dream Team at the 2004 Olympic Games.
But my favorite is the Pan-American Games in Cuba in 1991, when we won the gold and we put a bullet in the United States team, which was quite similar to the one that had won the bronze during the World.
